                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/911.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Consul at Douglas</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-07T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1912—12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President has excepted the arms and ammunition referred to and shipment is
                    already en route. Meet shipment at Douglas and make necessary arrangements for
                    its immediate and safe transshipment to destination under escort if possible via
                    Naco, where customs officials have been appropriately instructed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
